%F A118375 a(n) = T(n) + e(n), where T(n) = n(n+1)(n+2)/6 = A000292(n) is the tetrahedral numbers and e(n) = 0 if n = 0,1 (mod 4) and 1 if n = 2,3 (mod 4). (Published by Rob Johnson in sci.math.)
